question:
District category contains Administrative District, Business District, Automotive District, and Single-family Homes.
Supermarkets category contains Dollar General, Kroger, Peapod, and ShopRite.
Product category contains Danish Pastries, Canned Pineapple, and Whipped Cream.
The number of each Administrative District 's Kroger equals each ShopRite 's Product.
The number of each Administrative District 's Dollar General equals each Single-family Homes 's Kroger.
The number of each Dollar General 's Danish Pastries equals 9.
The number of each Peapod 's Danish Pastries equals 10 more than each Kroger 's Canned Pineapple.
The number of each Dollar General 's Canned Pineapple equals 0 more than each Administrative District 's Kroger.
The number of each Single-family Homes 's ShopRite equals each Single-family Homes 's Dollar General.
The number of each Kroger 's Canned Pineapple equals 16 times each Administrative District 's Dollar General.
The number of each Peapod 's Whipped Cream equals each Automotive District 's ShopRite.
The number of each Business District 's Peapod equals 5.
The number of each Business District 's Dollar General equals 20.
The number of each Single-family Homes 's Dollar General equals 17 times each Business District 's ShopRite.
The number of each Single-family Homes 's Kroger equals 13.
The number of each Business District 's ShopRite equals 0 more than each Administrative District 's Dollar General.
The number of each ShopRite 's Whipped Cream equals each Single-family Homes 's ShopRite.
The number of each Peapod 's Canned Pineapple equals 2 times each Dollar General 's Danish Pastries.
The number of each Automotive District 's ShopRite equals 17.
How many Kroger does Administrative District have?
solution:
Define each Single-family Homes 's Kroger as D; So D = 13.
Define each Administrative District 's Dollar General as r; So r = D = 13.
Define each Business District 's ShopRite as T; So T = 0 + r = 0 + 13 = 13.
Define each Single-family Homes 's Dollar General as G; So G = 17 * T = 17 * 13 = 14.
Define each Single-family Homes 's ShopRite as e; So e = G = 14.
Define each ShopRite 's Whipped Cream as g; So g = e = 14.
Define each ShopRite 's Product as z; So z = g = 14.
Define each Administrative District 's Kroger as M; So M = z = 14.
